@entrypoint
Feature: Entrypoint — Config Loading, Validation, and Generation Loop Orchestration
  As a pipeline operator
  I want agent.py to load configuration, validate all prerequisites, and orchestrate the generation loop
  So that the pipeline starts reliably, fails fast on misconfiguration, and runs to completion with resilience

  Background:
    Given a valid agent-config.yaml in the working directory
    And a domain directory matching the configured domain name
    And a GOAL.md file within the domain directory
    And a ChromaDB collection populated with chunks for the domain

  # ━━ GROUP A: Key Examples ━━

  # Why: Core startup — config loaded and parsed into structured dataclasses
  @key-example @smoke
  Scenario: Loading a valid agent-config.yaml
    Given an agent-config.yaml with domain, player, coach, generation, chunking, and logging sections
    When the entrypoint loads configuration
    Then an AgentConfig should be returned with all sections populated
    And the Player ModelConfig should reflect the configured provider, model, endpoint, and temperature
    And the Coach ModelConfig should reflect the configured provider, model, endpoint, and temperature

  # Why: Core startup — structured JSON logging configured before any other output
  @key-example @smoke
  Scenario: Structured logging is configured from the config file
    Given an agent-config.yaml with logging level "INFO" and format "json"
    When the entrypoint starts up
    Then structured JSON logging should be active
    And the log level should be set to INFO

