  # ━━ GROUP D: Edge Cases ━━

  # Why: Resume mode — skip clean, read checkpoint, continue from saved index (ADR-ARCH-010)
  @edge-case
  Scenario: Resuming from a checkpoint after a previous crash
    Given a previous run completed 800 of 1000 targets
    And output/.checkpoint contains the value 800
    When the entrypoint starts with --resume
    Then the output directory should not be cleaned
    And generation should resume from target 801

  # Why: Resume without checkpoint file — should fail clearly, not silently start fresh
  @edge-case @negative
  Scenario: Resume requested but no checkpoint file exists
    Given no output/.checkpoint file exists
    When the entrypoint starts with --resume
    Then an error should be raised indicating no checkpoint is available to resume from

  # Why: Fresh start cleans output directory (ADR-ARCH-008)
  @edge-case
  Scenario: Fresh start cleans the output directory
    Given output files exist from a previous run
    When the entrypoint starts without --resume
    Then the output directory should be cleaned before generation begins

  # Why: Default config values applied when optional fields omitted
  @edge-case
  Scenario: Default values are applied for optional generation config fields
    Given an agent-config.yaml with only domain, player provider, player model, coach provider, and coach model specified
    When the entrypoint loads configuration
    Then max_turns should default to 3
    And llm_retry_attempts should default to 3
    And llm_retry_backoff should default to 2.0
    And llm_timeout should default to 300
    And target_timeout should default to 600
    And chunk_size should default to 512
    And overlap should default to 64
    And log level should default to INFO
    And log format should default to json

  # Why: Coach rejection at max_turns — target logged to rejected.jsonl
  @edge-case
  Scenario: Target rejected after exhausting all turns
    Given max_turns is set to 3
    And the Coach rejects the example on all 3 turns
    When the generation loop completes processing the target
    Then the target should be logged to rejected.jsonl
    And the next target should be processed

  # Why: Target timeout — generation takes too long, discard and continue (ADR-ARCH-010)
  @edge-case
  Scenario: Target exceeding the per-target timeout is discarded
    Given target_timeout is set to 600 seconds
    And a target takes longer than 600 seconds to process
    When the timeout is reached
    Then the target should be logged to rejected.jsonl with reason "timeout"
    And the next target should be processed

  # Why: LLM retry on transient failure (ADR-ARCH-010)
  @edge-case
  Scenario: Transient LLM failure is retried with exponential backoff
    Given llm_retry_attempts is set to 3 and llm_retry_backoff is 2.0
    And the LLM returns a transient error on the first call
    When the retry mechanism handles the failure
    Then the call should be retried after a backoff delay
    And if the retry succeeds the generation should continue normally

  # Why: All retries exhausted — target discarded, pipeline continues
  @edge-case
  Scenario: All LLM retries exhausted for a target
    Given llm_retry_attempts is set to 3
    And the LLM fails on all 3 retry attempts
    When all retries are exhausted
    Then the target should be logged to rejected.jsonl with the failure reason
    And the pipeline should continue to the next target

